This paper is about generative adversarial learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper proposes a new approach to deal with mode collapse in GANs, which is a common problem in this area. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) since the experiments involve real images. Other possible sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.GR (Graphics).
